This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it focuses on optimization in machine learning. The use of variance reduction techniques also suggests that it may belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. The algorithm proposed in the paper may also have applications in distributed computing (cs.DC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of asynchronous algorithms may suggest that it could also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
